    {
      "id": "bibop-allocation",
      "durationMs": 18000,
      "narration": {
        "text": "Allocation had a different problem. Every new object called malloc, zeroed memory, and searched for a tracking slot. The BiBOP heap groups one size class per page. Allocation becomes a pointer bump, while pages still come from the operating system."
