      "id": "limits-and-result",
      "durationMs": 20500,
      "narration": {
        "text": "The result is not that an AOT VM always beats a JIT. HotSpot still wins recursion and tight arithmetic. The useful result is narrower: client-sized memory, direct native access, and warmed-JVM throughput, for seventeen kilobytes of extra binary."
